During routine network monitoring, multiple anomalous activities were identified within a 10-minute packet capture. These included:

Port scanning behavior from an internal host
Repeated failed authentication attempts followed by a successful login
Periodic DNS queries exhibiting beaconing characteristics
Suspicious outbound HTTP traffic indicating possible data exfiltration

The combined evidence suggests a multi-stage attack scenario, potentially involving reconnaissance, brute-force compromise, command-and-control (C2) communication, and data exfiltration.

